description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mental Health Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Health care are currently recruiting a Support Worker role to join our team at Cygnet Hospital Kewstoke.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an exceptionally caring individual who really wants to go above and beyond for the patients in our care,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role you’ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Offer enhanced care with a flexible learning approach for all our patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Work in the hospital area, providing guidance and encouragement to patients through physical and emotional support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Maintain a safe, clean and enjoyable environment to live and work in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Assist patients with their medical and welfare needs and report as required&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Safeguard patients&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Learn about individuals’ specific needs and provide help in the most appropriate way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Answer Nurse Call System (where applicable), giving assistance as required, as well as answering the door and telephone appropriately.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; •Carry out regular checks on residents at intervals determined by trained Staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; •Work both day &amp; night shifts&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We&#39;re looking for people who have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Excellent communication skills and the ability to be a good team player&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• The sensitivity and energy required to provide a trusting, stimulating and varied lifestyle for the residents&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• A genuine desire to make a real difference in people’s lives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Experience within a rehabilitation setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; •Previous experience in the care of Mental Health/Learning Disability/Autism residents/clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; •Previous experience in care environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In return we’ll offer you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Opportunity for overtime&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• NHS discount&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• DBS paid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Free uniform&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Regular coaching and support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Opportunity to undertake further learning with our excellent apprenticeship scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Subsidised meals on duty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note: successful candidates will be required to undergo an enhanced DBS check.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Do you want a career that inspires people? Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
